(cid:64)(cid:48)(cid:53)(cid:50)(cid:63)(cid:50)(cid:63)(cid:67)(cid:54)(cid:57)(cid:57)(cid:50)(cid:13)
WESTFIEL(cid:49) *location opened inf(cid:13)iscal 202(cid:32)Letter to Shareholders
“As I look ahead, I’m even more excited about our future. Portillo’s has a long runway, and
I look forward sharing the story of our brand and its development with you as we bring our
amazing Chicago-style street food to more guests across the country.”
May 11, 2023
PORTILLO’S SHAREHOLDERS:
On April 5, 2023, Portillo’s celebrated its 60th anniversary. I’ve heard from so many shareholders with a
lifetime of Portillo’s memories. For some, it began at our original trailer, The Dog House. Others share stories
of visits that spanned generations, with Portillo’s as the go-to place for family gatherings. Still others are
newer fans who have discovered Portillo’s as we’ve moved into additional states.
For six decades, Portillo’s has ignited the senses of our obsessed fans by creating unrivaled experiences. It’s
core to who we are – and it’s what we will continue to do.
As I look back on our first full year as a public company, I’m proud of the progress we’ve made. We
weathered unprecedented inflationary pressure, navigated a tight labor market, and dealt with industry-wide
permitting and construction delays while continuing to deliver the food and experience that make Portillo’s
great. We also looked for opportunities to get even better, increasing operational efficiency and sustaining
best-in-class team member retention. We invested in the guest experience and continued to add innovative
menu items like the Garden Dog, our plant-based Chicago-style hot dog. If you haven’t tried a Garden Dog
yet, I highly recommend adding it to your next order. It continues to be a hit for both longtime Portillo’s
fans – including meat eaters – and new guests who have something on our menu just for them. With these
changes, and our focus on operational excellence to create an unrivaled experience, our guests are even
more satisfied than before.
As I look ahead, I’m even more excited about our future. Portillo’s has a long runway, and I look forward
sharing the story of our brand and its development with you as we bring our amazing Chicago-style street
food to more guests across the country.
We’ve committed to delivering same-restaurant sales growth in the low-single digits, as it’s important that
our existing restaurant base continues to thrive. But adding new restaurants at 10% per year will be a major
driver of the high-single to low double-digit annual revenue growth rate we’ve targeted as our longer-term
objective. As we continue to grow, we’re thrilled to keep finding new fans across the nation who enjoy our
diverse menu of Chicago-style street food and resonate with our fun, high-energy atmosphere.Although it’s still early, we’re thrilled to see that our “Class of 2022” is already exceeding its underwriting
expectations. While we know we have a dedicated fan base in Chicagoland, the successful openings in The
Colony in Texas; Schererville, IN; and Tucson and Gilbert, AZ, prove that Portillo’s is a brand that travels well.
In its first month of operation, for example, The Colony averaged $48,000 sales per day while delivering
outstanding guest satisfaction scores. This reinforces our confidence in our national expansion strategy,
which will generate attractive returns both for us and you, our investors. We’ve committed to expanding our
restaurant base by at least 10% per year, which gets us to at least 600 locations over the next 25 years.
Finally, it must be noted that Portillo’s has some of the best Team Members in the restaurant industry. Our
restaurants, both new and existing, are known for their incredibly high volumes. Our guests can get their
Portillo’s the way they want it – dine-in, takeout, drive-thru, delivery, catering and shipping – because our
incredible Team Members make it happen. They are committed to making Portillo’s an oasis for guests, and
I’m so proud of how they deliver the Portillo’s experience at our restaurants.
Our teams are excited and having fun, leading Portillo’s to have some of the lowest turnover numbers in the
restaurant industry. That’s because of our belief that people are the heart of Portillo’s. We were recognized
in 2022 as an employer of choice, winning Best Places to Work awards from both QSR Magazine and Best in
Biz Awards, thanks in part to our commitment to treat our Team Members like family and keep investing in
them. Our engaged Team Members take care of our guests, who in turn drive the best economic results
for everyone.
With this strong team behind me, I’m confident in all the commitments we’ve made. We have performed as
a brand, and we continue to get even better. We do this by living our values of Family, Greatness, Energy and
Fun every day in our restaurants, at our plants, and at our Restaurant Support Center. By staying true to our
mission of creating lifelong memories, we’re able to create value for our three core constituents: our team
members, our guests, and you, our shareholders.
We’re excited that you’ll get to be there as we bring the Portillo’s experience to a new generation of Portillo’s
fans, including in states like Arizona, Florida, Texas and beyond.
Thank you for being an important part of the Portillo’s journey.
Michael Osanloo,
